---
layout: base
title: Reading calendar
description: A personal calendar of the articles you've read, drawn from this device's local reading history.
permalink: /reading-calendar/
---
<main class="container reading-cal" data-pagefind-ignore>

  <header class="reading-cal__header">
    <p class="reading-cal__kicker">Reader tools</p>
    <h1 class="reading-cal__title">Reading calendar</h1>
    <p class="reading-cal__lede">
      The articles you&rsquo;ve read, by date. Switch between day,
      week, month, and year views &mdash; click any day in the grid
      to drill in. Drawn entirely from this device&rsquo;s local
      history; no account, no server.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="reading-cal__summary" id="reading-cal-summary"></div>

  <div id="reading-cal-mount" class="cal-mount" aria-live="polite">
    <p class="cal-loading">Loading your reading history&hellip;</p>
  </div>

  {% include "partials/calendar-data.njk" %}

  <noscript>
    <p class="cal-noscript">
      The reading calendar reads your local history with JavaScript.
      Without JS the calendar can&rsquo;t render.
    </p>
  </noscript>

</main>

<script src="/assets/js/calendar-shared.js?v={{ buildTime }}" defer></script>
